Step 1: Install System Prerequisites (Offline)
📋 Instructions
Goal: To install git, python3, pip, and the C++ build-essential tools from the .deb files you downloaded onto your USB drive.

Plug your USB drive into your offline Ubuntu machine.

Open a terminal.

Find the path to your USB drive. It's usually mounted under /media/your_username/. You can use the ls /media/your_username/ command to see the name. Let's assume its name is MY_USB.

Navigate to the system_packages folder you created on the USB, which contains all the .deb files.

Run the apt install command using the . prefix. This tells apt to install all .deb files from the current directory (the . symbol) and to handle their dependencies correctly (which is why you downloaded them all).

This single command will install everything we need to build the Python environment.

💻 Commands
(Run these in your terminal)

Bash

# 1. Navigate to your USB folder
#    (Replace with your actual path)
cd /media/your_username/MY_USB/system_packages

# 2. Install all .deb files from this folder
#    This will ask for your password
sudo apt install ./*.deb
Once this is complete, git, pip, venv, and the C++ compiler are all installed on your offline system.
